A spinal intramedullary abscess secondary to an infected dermoid cyst is rare, 
and it has a poor prognosis, unless diagnosed and treated promptly. We report a 
12-month-old patient with a spinal intramedullary abscess with secondary to a 
dermoid cyst resulting from a dermal sinus, despite a clearly defined opening at 
the lower back with discharge of a purulent material from a dermal sinus tract 
